{"pageProps":{"tutorial":{"title":"CSS Backgrounds","slug":"css-backgrounds","subject":"CSS","category":"Web Development","level":"Beginner","estimated_read_time":"15 mins","prerequisites":["CSS Colors"],"learning_objectives":["Learn background-color","Learn background-image","Learn background-repeat","Learn background-attachment","Learn background-position","Learn the background shorthand property"],"theory":"The CSS background properties are used to define the background effects for elements.\n\n*   `background-color`: Sets the solid color.\n*   `background-image`: Specifies an image to use as the background.\n*   `background-repeat`: Sets if/how the image repeats (repeat-x, repeat-y, no-repeat).\n*   `background-attachment`: Specifies if the image scrolls with the page or is fixed.\n*   `background-position`: Specifies the position of the image (e.g., `center top`).","syntax":"body {\n  background-color: lightblue;\n  background-image: url(\"paper.gif\");\n  background-repeat: no-repeat;\n  background-position: right top;\n}","examples":[{"code":"/* Shorthand Syntax */\nbody {\n  background: #ffffff url(\"img_tree.png\") no-repeat right top;\n}","output":"Sets color, image, repeat, and position in one line.","explanation":"Order: color image repeat attachment position."}],"common_mistakes":[{"mistake":"Breaking image paths","correction":"Ensure the url path is correct relative to the CSS file.","example":"WRONG: url(image.png) when image is in a subfolder.\nCORRECT: url(images/image.png)"}],"interview_questions":[{"question":"How do you make a background image cover the entire element area without stretching distortion?","answer":"Use `background-size: cover;`.","difficulty":"Medium"}],"practice_problems":[{"problem":"Set a background image 'bg.jpg' that does not repeat.","hint":"Use background-repeat.","solution":"background-image: url('bg.jpg');\nbackground-repeat: no-repeat;","difficulty":"Easy"}],"real_world_use_cases":[{"scenario":"Hero Sections","descriptio